Thibaud Jean Vallet, 24, and his cousin Jean Mickael Batrikian, 18, pleaded guilty to animal cruelty after footage emerged of them lighting the quokka on Rottnest Island on April 3 .
The pair were ordered to pay $4000 and were told they would be held behind bars for seven days if they fail to pay the fine .
Animal rights activists have claimed the pair's punishment was too lenient for their crime .